<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idp151847632">
<term>Deep Throat</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm5575072">the anonymous source, later revealed to be associate director of the FBI Mark Felt, who supplied reporters Bob Woodward and Carl Bernstein with information about White House involvement in the Watergate break-in</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp269196480">
<term>executive privilege</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp275780704">the right of the U.S. president to refuse subpoenas requiring him to disclose private communications on the grounds that this might interfere with the functioning of the executive branch</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp223025504">
<term>plumbers</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp27329072">men used by the White House to spy on and sabotage President Nixon’s opponents and stop leaks to the press</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
